title: Georgia O’Keeffe Sky Above Clouds IV Scarf
description:
Scarf developed from Georgia O’Keeffe’s, Sky Above Clouds IV, 1965, from The Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

One of the most influential American artists of the 20th century, Georgia O’Keeffe promoted new ideas of abstraction and helped redefine modern art. Sky Above Clouds IV, was painted in the summer of 1965, when Georgia O’Keeffe was 77 years old. This monumental work culminates a series inspired by the artist’s experiences as an airplane passenger during the 1950s.

  • Dimensions: 25 x 72 in.
  • Material: 100% Polyester.
  • Hand Wash.
